The paper deals with the dynamics of information propagation on social networks, which is a topic that falls under the intersection of several CS sub-disciplines. The most likely category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), which specifically deals with the study of social networks and the flow of information within them. The paper also involves data analysis and modeling, which could place it under cs.SD (Software Development), as well as cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms), which deals with the efficient processing of large datasets. The study of social networks and information propagation also falls under cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences), while the use of social media data could place it under cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity).
